The contact rate decline was a dashboard bug, not a sales problem.

The old dashboard showed a cliff from 14.3% to 4.3%. After fixing the measurement, the real rate has been steady at 9–11% since Week 2.

The Problem

What the old dashboard showed

The old dashboard reported human contact rate falling from 14.3% to 4.3% — a dramatic collapse that suggested a serious performance problem.

Why it was wrong: On Feb 9, Adam started using 4 new call outcome labels. The old dashboard didn't map them — 27 real human contacts became invisible. At the same time, 9 calls were over-counted due to duration-based fallback.

The Correction

What the real numbers look like

After updating to the 10-category system, the contact rate has been stable at 9–11% from Week 2 through Week 5.
